statement.p:
First ask for circulation: \oint_{\partial R}\mathbf F\cdot d\mathbf r=\oint_{\partial R}xy\,dx+(x^2-y)\,dy. Here P=xy,\qquad Q=x^2-y. So Q_x-P_y=2x-x=x. Green's theorem gives
\oint_{\partial R}xy\,dx+(x^2-y)\,dy \amp= \iint_R x\,dA \amp= \int_0^2\int_0^1 x\,dy\,dx \amp= \int_0^2 x\,dx \amp= 2.
Thus \boxed{\text{circulation}=2.}

Now ask for outward flux: \oint_{\partial R}\mathbf F\cdot\mathbf n\,ds. The flux form is M\,dy-N\,dx=xy\,dy-(x^2-y)\,dx. Green's theorem in flux form gives \oint_{\partial R}\mathbf F\cdot\mathbf n\,ds=\iint_R(M_x+N_y)\,dA. Since M_x=y,\qquad N_y=-1, we get
\oint_{\partial R}\mathbf F\cdot\mathbf n\,ds \amp= \iint_R(y-1)\,dA \amp= \int_0^2\int_0^1(y-1)\,dy\,dx \amp= \int_0^2\left(\frac12-1\right)dx \amp= -1.
So \boxed{\text{outward flux}=-1.}

subsection.md:
\begin{array}{c|l}
\text{Check} \amp \text{What it protects} \\ \hline
\text{positive orientation} \amp \text{the sign of the boundary integral}\\[1mm]
\text{all boundary components} \amp \text{holes and inner boundaries}\\[1mm]
\omega \text{ is } C^1 \text{ near } R \amp \text{no hidden jumps or singularities}\\[1mm]
\partial R \text{ is piecewise smooth and finite} \amp \text{the boundary integral is a finite sum}
\end{array}

subsection.p:
Suppose a positively oriented boundary is written in polar form as x=r(\theta)\cos\theta,\qquad y=r(\theta)\sin\theta,\qquad 0\le \theta\le 2\pi. Then dx=(r'\cos\theta-r\sin\theta)\,d\theta and dy=(r'\sin\theta+r\cos\theta)\,d\theta. Compute the boundary form:
-y\,dx+x\,dy \amp= -r\sin\theta(r'\cos\theta-r\sin\theta)\,d\theta \amp\quad +r\cos\theta(r'\sin\theta+r\cos\theta)\,d\theta \amp= r^2(\sin^2\theta+\cos^2\theta)\,d\theta \amp= r^2\,d\theta.
Thus \boxed{\operatorname{Area}(R)=\frac12\int_0^{2\pi}r(\theta)^2\,d\theta.}

image.latex-image:
\begin{tikzpicture}[scale=0.7, >=stealth]
    \draw[->] (-4.5,0) -- (4.8,0) node[right] {\(x\)};
    \draw[->] (0,-4.5) -- (0,4.8) node[above] {\(y\)};

    \draw[gray!20, step=1] (-4,-4) grid (4,4);

    \draw[thick, fill=blue!8, domain=0:360, samples=360, smooth, variable=\t]
        plot ({(3+cos(3*\t))*cos(\t)}, {(3+cos(3*\t))*sin(\t)});

    % A clean, distinct orientation arrow hovering safely outside the boundary
    \draw[->, very thick, red!65!black]
        (15:4.4) arc[start angle=15, end angle=65, radius=4.4];

    \node at (0,-5.15) {\(r(\theta)=3+\cos(3\theta)\)};
\end{tikzpicture}
